com.thinkaurelius.titan.diskstorage.idmanagement

Class ConsistentKeyIDManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thinkaurelius.titan.diskstorage.idmanagement.AbstractIDManager
      • com.thinkaurelius.titan.diskstorage.idmanagement.ConsistentKeyIDManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDAuthority, BackendOperation.TransactionalProvider

    public class ConsistentKeyIDManager
extends AbstractIDManager
implements BackendOperation.TransactionalProvider
    IDAuthority implementation assuming that the backing store supports consistent key operations.

    ID blocks are allocated by first applying for an id block, waiting for a specified period of time and then checking that the application was the first received for that particular id block. If so, the application is considered successful. If not, some other process won the application and a new application is tried.

    The partition id is used as the key and since key operations are considered consistent, this protocol guarantees unique id block assignments.

    Author:
    Matthias Broecheler (me@matthiasb.com)

      • getIDBlock

        public long[] getIDBlock(int partition)
                  throws StorageException
        Description copied from interface: IDAuthority
        Returns an array that specifies a block of new ids, i.e. the ids between return[0] (inclusive) and return[1] (exclusive). It is guaranteed that the block of ids for the particular partition id is uniquely assigned, that is, the block of ids has not been previously and will not subsequently be assigned again when invoking this method on the local or any remote machine that is connected to the underlying storage backend.

        In other words, this method has to ensure that ids are uniquely assigned per partition.

        Specified by:
        getIDBlock in interface IDAuthority
        Parameters:
        partition - Partition for which to request an id block. Must be bigger or equal to 0
        Returns:
        a range of ids for the particular partition
        Throws:
        StorageException
